---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const CONTACT_EMAIL = "support@lifevisorapp.com";
const CONTROLLER_NAME = "Life Visor";
const EFFECTIVE_DATE = "2026-05-05";
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy — Life Visor" description="How Life Visor handles your data: stays on your device, no tracking, no servers.">
  <Navbar />

  <article class="w-full px-5 sm:px-8 py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
        <span class="block w-5 h-[2px] bg-muted-2"></span>
        <span class="eyebrow text-ink-soft">PRIVACY POLICY</span>
      </div>

      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-ink leading-[1.1] tracking-tight mb-4">
        Your data, <span class="highlight-yellow">your control</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-2 mb-12">Effective date: {EFFECTIVE_DATE}</p>

      <div class="prose-content space-y-6 text-base text-muted leading-relaxed">

        <p>
          {CONTROLLER_NAME} (“we,” “our,” or “us”) operates the Life Visor mobile application
          available on the Apple App Store and Google Play (the “App”) and the website
          <a href="https://www.lifevisorapp.com" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-4">lifevisorapp.com</a>
          (together, the “Service”). This Privacy Policy explains what information we process, why,
          and the rights you have. By using the Service, you agree to the practices described here.
        </p>
        <p>
          Life Visor is a privacy-first time-tracking app. Your activity data lives only on your
          device. We do not run servers that store, sync, or analyze it.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink pt-8">1. Data Controller</h2>
        <p>
          The data controller responsible for any personal data processed in connection with the
          Service is {CONTROLLER_NAME}. You can reach us at
          <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`} class="text-accent underline underline-offset-4">{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink pt-8">2. Information We Process</h2>

        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-ink pt-4">2.1 Information that stays on your device</h3>
        <p>
          When you use the App you create activities and sessions (names, colors, categories,
          start/end times). This information is stored exclusively in a local database on your
          device.
          <span class="font-semibold text-ink">It never leaves your device, is never transmitted to us, and is not accessible to anyone but you.</span>
          Uninstalling the App permanently removes this data.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-ink pt-4">2.2 Information processed by third-party processors</h3>
        <p>
          To enable Pro purchases and restore them across your devices, the App uses
          <span class="font-semibold text-ink">RevenueCat, Inc.</span> (a service provider acting
          on our behalf). RevenueCat receives:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>An anonymous, randomly generated user identifier (App User ID).</li>
          <li>Your purchase receipts as issued by Apple App Store or Google Play.</li>
          <li>Basic device information (operating system, App version, device model, country, language).</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          RevenueCat does not receive your name, email, phone number, or any of your activity data.
          For details, see RevenueCat's privacy policy at
          <a href="https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-4">revenuecat.com/privacy</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-ink pt-4">2.3 Payments</h3>
        <p>
          All payments are processed by <span class="font-semibold text-ink">Apple</span> (App
          Store) or <span class="font-semibold text-ink">Google</span> (Google Play). We never see
          or store your payment method, card number, or billing address. Their respective privacy
          policies apply to those transactions.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-ink pt-4">2.4 Notifications and Live Activities</h3>
        <p>
          On Android, the App can send you local reminders while a session is running. These
          notifications are scheduled and delivered locally by your device's operating system; no
          data is transmitted to us. You can disable notifications at any time in your system
          settings.
        </p>
        <p>
          On iOS, the App uses Live Activities to display your running session on the lock screen
          and Dynamic Island. Live Activities run locally and do not transmit any data outside
          your device.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-ink pt-4">2.5 Website</h3>
        <p>
          The website lifevisorapp.com is a static informational site hosted by a third-party
          provider. We do not use cookies, web analytics, or behavioral tracking on the website.
          Standard server access logs (IP address, request time, user agent) may be temporarily
          collected by the hosting provider for security and operational purposes.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink pt-8">3. Purposes and Legal Bases (GDPR)</h2>
        <p>
          For users located in the European Economic Area, the United Kingdom, or Switzerland, the
          following legal bases under Article 6 GDPR apply to the limited data processed via
          RevenueCat:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Performance of a contract</span> (Art. 6(1)(b)) — to validate purchases and provide Pro features.</li>
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Legitimate interests</span> (Art. 6(1)(f)) — to detect fraudulent purchases and maintain the integrity of the purchase system.</li>
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Legal obligation</span> (Art. 6(1)(c)) — to comply with tax, accounting and consumer-protection laws applicable to digital sales.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink pt-8">4. Categories of Recipients</h2>
        <p>
          We share the limited information described in section 2.2 with:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>RevenueCat, Inc. — purchase processing and entitlement management.</li>
          <li>Apple Inc. and Google LLC — payment processing and platform distribution.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not sell, rent, or share personal information with advertising networks, data
          brokers, or any other third parties.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink pt-8">5. International Data Transfers</h2>
        <p>
          RevenueCat, Apple and Google process data on servers located in the United States and
          other jurisdictions. Where personal data of users in the EEA, UK or Switzerland is
          transferred outside those regions, transfers are protected by appropriate safeguards,
          including the European Commission's Standard Contractual Clauses and, where applicable,
          the EU–U.S. Data Privacy Framework.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink pt-8">6. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          Your local activity data is retained on your device for as long as you keep the App
          installed. Uninstalling the App deletes it.
        </p>
        <p>
          Anonymous purchase records held by RevenueCat are retained for as long as required to
          maintain your entitlements and to comply with applicable tax and consumer-protection
          laws (typically up to 7 years).
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink pt-8">7. Your Privacy Rights</h2>

        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-ink pt-4">7.1 All users</h3>
        <p>
          You can delete all activity data we never see by simply uninstalling the App. To request
          deletion or export of any anonymous purchase data linked to your installation, contact
          us at <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`} class="text-accent underline underline-offset-4">{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>
          and include your store account email so the request can be matched.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-ink pt-4">7.2 EEA, UK and Switzerland (GDPR / UK GDPR)</h3>
        <p>
          You have the right to: access (Art. 15), rectification (Art. 16), erasure (Art. 17),
          restriction of processing (Art. 18), data portability (Art. 20), object to processing
          (Art. 21), and withdraw consent at any time (Art. 7) without affecting the lawfulness of
          processing carried out before withdrawal. You also have the right to lodge a complaint
          with your local data protection supervisory authority. A list of EU/EEA authorities is
          available at
          <a href="https://edpb.europa.eu/about-edpb/about-edpb/members_en" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-4">edpb.europa.eu</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-ink pt-4">7.3 California (CCPA / CPRA)</h3>
        <p>
          California residents have the right to: know what personal information we collect, the
          sources, purposes, and recipients; access and obtain a copy of that information; request
          deletion; request correction; opt out of any sale or sharing of personal information;
          and limit the use of sensitive personal information. You will not be discriminated
          against for exercising these rights.
        </p>
        <p>
          <span class="font-semibold text-ink">We do not sell or share your personal information</span>
          (as those terms are defined under the CCPA/CPRA), and we do not process sensitive
          personal information for purposes other than those expressly permitted by the regulation.
          Categories of personal information collected in the past 12 months are limited to:
          identifiers (anonymous user ID), commercial information (purchase records), and internet
          or other electronic network activity (basic device information transmitted with
          purchase events). To exercise your rights, contact
          <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`} class="text-accent underline underline-offset-4">{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-ink pt-4">7.4 Brazil (LGPD)</h3>
        <p>
          Brazilian users have the rights set out in Article 18 of the LGPD, including
          confirmation of processing, access, correction, anonymization or deletion of unnecessary
          data, portability, information about sharing, and revocation of consent.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-ink pt-4">7.5 Other regions</h3>
        <p>
          If your jurisdiction provides additional rights (e.g. Canada PIPEDA, Australia Privacy
          Act, India DPDP Act), you may exercise them by contacting us. We will respond within the
          timeframes required by applicable law.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink pt-8">8. No Tracking</h2>
        <p>
          Life Visor does not track you across apps or websites. We do not use analytics SDKs,
          advertising networks, behavioral trackers, or device fingerprinting. We do not request
          the App Tracking Transparency permission on iOS, and we do not access your advertising
          identifier on Android.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink pt-8">9. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Life Visor is rated for general audiences (4+ in most regions, with equivalent ratings
          in other markets) and may be used by children with the permission of a parent or
          guardian. Because all activity data stays on the device and the App does not request any
          personal information (name, email, age, location, contacts, etc.), children's privacy is
          protected by design.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 (or the
          equivalent minimum age in your jurisdiction). If you are a parent or guardian and
          believe your child has provided personal information to us, please contact
          <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`} class="text-accent underline underline-offset-4">{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>
          and we will take appropriate action.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink pt-8">10. Security</h2>
        <p>
          Because activity data is stored only on your device, its security is primarily protected
          by your device's operating system (sandboxing, full-disk encryption, screen lock).
          Communications with RevenueCat, Apple and Google are encrypted in transit using TLS. No
          method of transmission or storage is 100% secure, but we work with reputable processors
          that follow industry-standard practices.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink pt-8">11. Data Deletion</h2>
        <p>
          To delete all activity data, simply uninstall the App. To request deletion of anonymous
          purchase data held by RevenueCat, email
          <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`} class="text-accent underline underline-offset-4">{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>
          from the email associated with your Apple ID or Google account so we can match the
          request. We will action verified deletion requests within 30 days.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink pt-8">12. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy when our practices change or when required by law.
          Material changes will be reflected by an updated effective date at the top of this page.
          We encourage you to review this policy periodically.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink pt-8">13. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy-related questions, requests, or complaints, contact us at
          <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`} class="text-accent underline underline-offset-4">{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
          We are not currently required to appoint a Data Protection Officer, but the contact
          above serves as our designated privacy contact for all matters covered by this policy.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
